Reasoning: The paper deals with graph theory and computational complexity, which are common topics in computer science. The problem studied in the paper, Strong Triadic Closure (STC), is a well-known problem in graph theory and falls under the category of graph algorithms. The paper also introduces several generalizations of STC, which involve multiple edge colors and additional constraints on the permitted colors for each edge. These generalizations are likely to be of interest to researchers in the areas of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), graph theory (cs.GT), computational complexity (cs.CC), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
